Definition: marked by skill in deception
Example: cunning men often pass for wise; deep political machinations; a foxy scheme; a slick evasive answer; sly as a fox; tricky Dick; a wily old attorney
Synonyms: noun, cognition, craft, craftiness, cunning, dodgy, dodge, foxy, person, fox, foxiness, guileful, knavish, slick, communication, slickness, attribute, sly, slyness, tricksy, act, trick, tricky, trickiness, wily, wile, wiliness, marked, by, skill, in, deception, men, often, pass, for, wise, deep, political, machinations, a, scheme, evasive, answer, as, Dick, old, attorney
Category: adj.all
